<section id="tribal-leadership" class="bg-weave-pattern w-full py-12 md:py-24">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
    <div class="grid items-center gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Square image of Tribal Chief and Princess together -->
      <div class="animate-on-scroll flex justify-center">
        <div class="relative">
          <div
            class="aspect-square w-full max-w-[600px] overflow-hidden rounded-lg border-4 border-white shadow-lg"
          >
            <img
              src="/astro-app/chiefprincess.webp"
              alt="Tribal Chief and Princess"
              class="h-full w-full object-cover"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Welcome message and invitation -->
      <div
        class="animate-on-scroll space-y-6 rounded-lg bg-black/50 p-6 shadow-lg backdrop-blur-lg"
      >
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-white sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl"
        >
          Halito!
        </h2>

        <p class="text-muted">
          Greetings from the Choctaw Indian Reservation. We invite you to join
          us for our annual Choctaw Indian Fair. The fair takes place on our
          centuries-old homeland in beautiful Choctaw, Mississippi. We gather
          each July to celebrate our heritage and share our beautiful and
          vibrant culture with our friends and neighbors. This year’s fair theme
          is:
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-xl font-bold text-white sm:text-3xl">
          The Choctaw Spirit Lives On
        </p>

        <p class="text-muted">
          Fairgoers will experience the magnificent journey of our people
          through historical and cultural displays, social dancing, tribal arts
          & crafts, Choctaw stickball – the granddaddy of all field sports – as
          well as the Choctaw Indian Princess Pageant and traditional Choctaw
          food. The fair also offers carnival rides and games for the young and
          old alike, Shawi’s Discovery Zone and chart-topping musical acts each
          night. There’s something for everyone at the Choctaw Indian Fair –
          we’ll see you soon!
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-white sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl"
        >
          Yakoki!
        </h2>

